				 Lock Timeouts &amp; Memory (Dear SQL DBA Episode 37) 

				 
					 April 6, 2017 Kendra Little Dear SQL DBA ,  Locking 1  Comment 				 
			 
		 

			 
 The dev server got bogged down during a deployment and lock timeouts were everywhere. Was the perfmon counter way off about how much memory was being used just for locks? 
 In this 19 minute episode… 
 00:33 What’s new @ SQL Workbooks: Down the Rabbit Hole 
 03:00 This week’s question about lock timeouts &amp; memory in SQL Server 
